The paper discusses the theoretical performance examination of lookahead search in game playing, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of search trees and optimization functions also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the examination of interactive behaviors and the application of the method in various settings suggest a connection to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
